Value.value: The taproom is gloomy and quiet, with only a few patrons in evidence. The floor is sticky underfoot, the walls grimy with the smoke of hearthfires past, and the air is thick with the sour smell of stale beer. The barkeep looks up hopefully at your entrance.
A few small sounds penetrate the gloom - the rattle of dice in a cup, beer dripping from a loose spigot. You hear the occasional soft scrape of armoured boots from the corner.
The only danger here is from mercenaries in their cups. This place has seen better days.
